{"repo": "jazzband/dj-database-url", "pull_number": 285, "instance_id": "jazzband__dj-database-url-285", "issue_numbers": [283], "base_commit": "36ec238b03d31baf9d295683b73176d7d99a6de6", "patch": "diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml\nindex 6cf3f6c..23be009 100644\n--- a/pyproject.toml\n+++ b/pyproject.toml\n@@ -41,7 +41,7 @@ build-backend = \"uv_build\"\n [tool.uv.build-backend]\n module-name = \"dj_database_url\"\n module-root = \"\"\n-source-include = [\"dj_database_url/py.typed\"]\n+source-include = [\"dj_database_url/py.typed\", \"tests\"]\n \n [tool.black]\n skip-string-normalization = 1\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "3.1.0 source distribution is missing tests\nThe 3.1.0 source distribution has lost the `tests` directory, which is [needed for downstream packaging](https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/discussions/downstream-packaging/#provide-complete-source-distributions). Please readd it.\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "I've opened a PR to fix this #285\n\nAdded \"tests\" to the source-include list in pyproject.toml since this project uses uv_build as the build backend.\nThanks.\nI'm sorry to say but this doesn't seem to have worked. 3.1.1 now has only an empty `tests` directory.\nApologies, it looks like i made a mistake in the original build which resulted in the directory being added but not the test source files. This will be fixed and released in the coming days.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/jazzband/dj-database-url/commit/581cf838c33db46acd2d576238e1c79d760d3cac"], "created_at": "2026-01-04T20:02:32Z"}
